9. Output files written by the current gridless implementation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

9.1 Cutoff-rigidity mode
------------------------

Primary outputs written by the current code are:

  cutoff_gridless_points.dat
      Point list results (POINTS mode).

  cutoff_gridless_shells.dat
      Shell-grid results (SHELLS mode).

Optional / benchmark-style outputs may also be written in specific branches:

  cutoff_gridless_dir_map_point_####.dat
      Directional cutoff maps for individual points when enabled.

  cutoff_gridless_points_dipole_compare.dat
  cutoff_gridless_shells_dipole_compare.dat
      Comparison products used for dipole / analytic benchmarking.


9.2 Density / spectrum mode
---------------------------

Primary outputs written by the current code are:

  gridless_points_density.dat
      Total number density per point.

  gridless_points_spectrum.dat
      Energy-resolved transmissivity and local spectrum per point.

  gridless_points_flux.dat
      Total integral flux plus optional user-defined energy channels.

  gridless_shell_<ALT>km_density_channels.dat
      Shell-grid density output with multiple Tecplot zones, including total
      density and channel-resolved contributions.

Optional dipole-comparison files may be written by benchmark paths:

  density_gridless_points_dipole_compare.dat
  spectrum_gridless_points_dipole_compare.dat
  flux_gridless_points_dipole_compare.dat
  density_gridless_shells_dipole_compare.dat
  spectrum_gridless_shells_dipole_compare.dat
  flux_gridless_shells_dipole_compare.dat

