10. Parallelism
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The gridless branch is designed to exploit both MPI and OpenMP where available.

MPI
---

Both major gridless solvers use dynamic point-level MPI scheduling so that slow
points (for example near penumbra-like access transitions or long-lived trapped
orbits) do not idle the rest of the job.

OpenMP
------

Density/spectrum mode contains OpenMP-aware logic for embarrassingly parallel
loops over energies and/or directions. Care is taken to avoid pathological nested
parallelism.

The exact runtime benefit depends strongly on field model, observation geometry,
energy range, and near-cutoff trajectory behavior.

